snippet.textDisplay:
2:00 And that is your so-called "CLUTCH KING" ???


Here is break down of why LBJ is not clutch overrated.


1. In the last 30 seconds of the game, if the score is tight and LBJ's team has possesion, LBJ holds the ball for 20 sec.
2. Then he tries to drive in
3. When defenders gets to LBJ, he delivers a kickout pass to outside shooter.
4. IF the shooter makes the shot, Fans says "OMG What a PASS MASTER! LBJ is so good at passing" IF the shooter misses "Fxxx that shooter, he sucks blah blah blah"


5. IF Lebron's lose the game, because he didnt show up in clutch moment, Media doesnt post a single thing about the game. (Just like Bleachers Report didnt post anything about LAL vs BKN game today on Facebook)
6. IF Lebron's team win, Media suddenly posts hundreds of videos even if it is about a normal pass that average NBA players do on a daily basis, and writes captions like "KING!" "CLUTCH" "MVP".


SO, people who doesnt always follow the game, or misses the game, only sees the great part of LeBron.


Which is why it is not totally wrong to say LeBron overrated, although he is great player and definitely top 10 all time.
